HEADWORD: Metanauplius
<hw>Met`a*nau"pli*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Meta-</er>, and <er>Nauplius</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
larval crustacean in a stage following the nauplius, and having about
seven pairs of appendages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

